'''GRB 110328A'''是由[[雨燕卫星|雨燕卫星]]于2011年3月28日探测到的[[伽玛射线暴|伽玛射线暴]]（gamma-ray burst，GRB），这也是在至今探测到持续时间最长的一次伽玛射线暴<ref>{{cite web |last=Smith |first=Stephen |title=Down the Barrel |url=http://www.thunderbolts.info/tpod/2011/arch11/110411barrel.htm |accessdate=2011-04-22 |date=2011-04-11 |archive-date=2020-07-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200711212735/http://www.thunderbolts.info/tpod/2011/arch11/110411barrel.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。这次伽玛射线暴发生在[[天龙座|天龙座]]一个小[[星系|星系]]的中心，距离地球约38亿[[光年|光年]]<ref>{{cite web|title=GRB 110328A: Chandra Observes Extraordinary Event|url=http://chandra.harvard.edu/photo/2011/grb110328/|publisher=Harvard-Smithsonian Center for Astrophysics|accessdate=2011-04-21|archive-date=2012-05-12|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/67cG9Jsz4?url=http://chandra.harvard.edu/photo/2011/grb110328/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

科学家认为这种极端异常的能量释放，可能是由星系中心附近一个[[超重黑洞|大质量黑洞]]利用其强大的[[潮汐力|潮汐力]]撕裂了一颗靠近它的[[恒星|恒星]]引发的，黑洞产生了两束剧烈的喷流，而其中一束恰好正对着地球<ref>{{cite web|last=Barres de Almeida and De Angelis|title=Enhanced emission from GRB 110328A could be evidence for tidal disruption of a star|url=http://xxx.lanl.gov/abs/1104.2528|publisher=arXiv:astro-ph|date=2011-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Coco |first=Alejandro |title=The Most Intense Cosmic Explosion Ever Seen |url=http://scienceray.com/physics/the-most-intense-cosmic-explosion-ever-seen/ |accessdate=2011-04-22 |publisher=Scienceray |date=2011-04-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120715005900/http://scienceray.com/physics/the-most-intense-cosmic-explosion-ever-seen/ |archivedate=2012-07-15 }}</ref><ref name=physorg061611>{{cite web|last=University of California|first=Berkeley|title=Unusual gamma-ray flash may have come from star being eaten by massive black hole|url=http://www.physorg.com/news/2011-06-unusual-gamma-ray-star-eaten-massive.html|publisher=PhysOrg|accessdate=16 June 2011|archive-date=2019-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191016220128/https://phys.org/news/2011-06-unusual-gamma-ray-star-eaten-massive.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

